title: database hard disk usage
body:
After updating erigon, the size of the database has increased from 1.45T to 2.0T. why?

flags: ` --prune=hrtc --chain=bsc`

```bash
> git reset --hard
HEAD is now at c67d4d14e better logging

> du -h ~/.local/share/erigon
3.7M	/root/.local/share/erigon/nodes/eth66
3.7M	/root/.local/share/erigon/nodes
2.1G	/root/.local/share/erigon/parlia
2.1G	/root/.local/share/erigon/txpool
4.0K	/root/.local/share/erigon/etl-temp
4.0K	/root/.local/share/erigon/snapshots
2.0T	/root/.local/share/erigon/chaindata
2.0T	/root/.local/share/erigon

```

Likely it's because of recent change in DB format: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/pull/3654
In Erigon we have way to store DB inserts more compact if they happen in sorted order. 
And during normal sync - it's done in sorted order.
But it was impossible to implement db migration in sorted order - and it lead to ~40% bigger BlockTransaction table.
If do sync from scratch you will end up with compact representation.

To proof you can do:
```
make db-tools
./build/bin/mdbx_stat -ef <your_datadir>/chaindata
./build/bin/mdbx_stat -s BlockTransaction <your_datadir>/chaindata
```
normally that table it's ~900Gb on BSC (if I remember right)
